  "2026-05-03T13:34:41.813Z",codex-audit,"Duplicate-check evidence: pm search history stream redaction command redact private path history drift --limit 10 found only closed history/security items; current audit discovered remaining private remote paths in historical JSONL streams after current item docs were sanitized."
  "2026-05-09T11:21:19.310Z",codex-agent,"2026-05-09 duplicate-check evidence: pm search tracker history privacy redaction private paths --limit 10 found this existing item as the canonical match. Current scan found no raw IP/password/token values in non-history tracked files; current pm item files only mention Sentry token variable names, but historical JSONL streams still include private remote paths from older telemetry operations. Do not hand-edit history; implement audited redaction support or migrate history safely."
  "2026-05-09T11:46:59.452Z",codex-agent,"Evidence 2026-05-09: privacy scan confirmed current tracked source/docs/workflows and current item files do not contain raw host/IP/password/token values from this request, but older append-only history streams still contain private infrastructure paths. This remains open because current pm policy forbids direct history rewrites; next work must add an audited redaction command or equivalent safe migration."
  "2026-05-09T13:30:10.115Z",codex-agent,"Scope decision recorded: executing direct one-off scrub for current tracked history/item artifacts now, with policy to redact all [redacted_path_prefix] path references in tracked pm artifacts for this run."
  "2026-05-09T13:42:44.553Z",codex-agent,"Direct one-off scrub complete for current tracked pm artifacts: redacted all [redacted_path_prefix] path literals plus lingering host-user literals across targeted .toon/history/managed-extension files. Verification scans now return zero matches in .agents/pm for [redacted_path_prefix], [redacted_user_at_host], and concrete private IP literals ([redacted_ip_pattern])."
  "2026-05-09T13:58:47.018Z",codex-agent,"Additional hardening completed in this remediation run: scripts/check-secrets now detects absolute home-path and user@private-host leakage patterns (with test/example exclusions), and Sentry scrub logic now redacts nested path-bearing payload fields so newly emitted events store [scrubbed_path] instead of local filesystem paths. This supports current-tree direct scrub governance while a first-class history redaction command remains open scope."
  "2026-05-11T23:04:58.790Z",codex-agent,"Validation follow-up 2026-05-12: package-first run fixed the only missing closed-item resolution metadata (pm-dhie), but pm validate --check-history-drift still reports the known five hash mismatches: pm-54d, pm-f3q4, pm-fdla, pm-mb4n, pm-tq1. This remains the canonical open audited history-redaction/drift blocker; no direct history edits were made in this package slice."
  "2026-05-12T05:29:03.212Z",codex-agent,"Audit update: post-package-refactor validate/health still show only the existing history hash mismatches for pm-54d, pm-f3q4, pm-fdla, pm-mb4n, and pm-tq1. Resolution metadata is clean; this remains the canonical blocker for history drift rather than a new package-refactor regression."
  "2026-05-16T16:48:23.271Z",codex-agent,"Audit update 2026-05-16: pm validate --check-resolution is clean after metadata backfill; remaining validation/health warnings are hash drift on pm-54d, pm-7vm9, pm-f3q4, pm-fdla, pm-mb4n, and pm-tq1. Keeping this as the canonical audited history redaction/drift follow-up."
  "2026-05-16T20:47:15.075Z",codex-agent,"Privacy evidence 2026-05-16: tracked secret scan passed and targeted scan found no raw host/password/token literals outside ignored private telemetry operations files. Current health/validate still reports only known history drift on pm-54d, pm-7vm9, pm-f3q4, pm-fdla, pm-mb4n, and pm-tq1; keeping this canonical redaction/history-drift item open."
  "2026-05-16T23:19:49.997Z",codex-agent,"Privacy audit 2026-05-17: read-only sub-agent scan covered 1905 tracked files and 745 tracked pm history files. node scripts/check-secrets.mjs passed; targeted scans found no concrete private IPv4 literals, no /home paths in tracked pm history, and no actual credential material beyond scanner regex literals. Remaining concern is operational metadata in append-only history, so this existing item remains the canonical redaction/history artifact follow-up; no duplicate privacy item created."
  "2026-05-17T00:05:14.137Z",codex-agent,"Privacy audit 2026-05-17: read-only sub-agent scan ran tracked-file and pm-history checks including scripts/check-secrets, private IPv4 patterns, absolute /home or /Users paths, user@host literals, credential assignment patterns, and scripts/prod tracking. Result: no new raw credential/password/private-IP/user@host/home-path leak found in tracked tree; git ls-files scripts/prod returned empty. Known history drift remains on pm-54d, pm-7vm9, pm-f3q4, pm-fdla, pm-mb4n, and pm-tq1; keeping this item as canonical rather than creating a duplicate."
  "2026-05-17T00:21:38.601Z",codex-agent,"Privacy sub-agent finding 2026-05-17: no raw credential/private key/private-IP/user@host leaks found; scripts/check-secrets passes and scripts/prod is untracked. Real tracked risk is legacy pm item/history text exposing operational telemetry/Sentry/Grafana metadata and token-scope details. Applying narrow redaction to current item files and mirrored history streams as authorized by user; product telemetry endpoint constants are left unchanged as intentional public config."
  "2026-05-17T09:28:30.316Z",codex-agent,"Startup pass cross-check 2026-05-17: reran tracked-file + .agents/pm privacy scans while validating pm-gt82 changes; no new key/private-token/private-IP/home-path leak introduced. Remaining hits are prior policy-discussion strings (for example user@private-host wording) rather than credential payloads."
  "2026-05-17T12:23:20.996Z",codex-agent,"Implementation complete: added native history-redact mutation command with repeatable --literal/--regex matchers, deterministic history rewrite, hash-chain recomputation, verification, audit marker entry (op=history_redact), ownership/lock governance checks, dry-run preview, MCP runAction support, CLI contracts exposure, and completion/docs updates. Added/updated coverage in unit+integration suites (history/activity, validate drift compatibility, contracts flags, completion command list/description, release-readiness help+coverage allowlist)."
  "2026-05-17T12:23:27.941Z",codex-agent,"Verification evidence: (1) targeted tests passed: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/history-activity-command.spec.ts tests/unit/validate-command.spec.ts tests/unit/contracts-command.spec.ts tests/unit/completion-command.spec.ts tests/integration/release-readiness-runtime.spec.ts (191/191). (2) isolated history-redact dogfood in temp PM_PATH passed with changed=true, replacements=2, audit_entry_added=true, pm history --verify ok=true, pm validate --check-history-drift status=ok. (3) node scripts/dogfood-package-first.mjs passed (ok=true, commands=54). (4) node scripts/check-secrets.mjs passed with no credential-like findings. (5) node scripts/release/sentry-telemetry-gate.mjs --telemetry-mode required --max-critical 10 --max-high 20 --json passed: Sentry critical=0 high=0 total=0; telemetry finish_error_rate_pct≈2.1 and failures_without_error_code_rows=0. (6) node scripts/release/run-gates.mjs --telemetry-mode required --json passed all checks including coverage 1330/1330 tests and 100% statement/branch/function/line coverage."
  "2026-05-17T14:11:36.390Z",codex-agent,"Continuation evidence 2026-05-17: this item was already in_progress with implementation comments, but fresh verification found pm history pm-xk39 --verify reports verify_failed:after_hash_mismatch:entry_9 while pm validate --check-history-drift reports 13 other drifted items and does not list pm-xk39. Keeping pm-xk39 active until the history verification gap is repaired or explicitly documented; not closing based on stale prior evidence."
  "2026-05-17T14:35:29.907Z",codex-agent,"Evidence 2026-05-17 continuation: history verification now returns structured diagnostics for patch-apply failures and full-chain mismatches instead of throwing or silently missing drift. pm validate --check-history-drift now reports 35 drifted items with 34 chain mismatches and 13 hash mismatches; pm health reports the same counts, and pm history pm-imob --verify --limit 1 returns verify_failed:patch_apply_failed:entry_13 as data. This item remains the canonical open history redaction/drift follow-up; not closing because the real repo still has legacy chain/hash drift to repair or explicitly migrate. No duplicate item created."
  "2026-05-17T19:01:26.400Z",claude-code-agent,"Session 14 (2026-05-17) audit: history-redact command verified working (pm history-redact --help renders, --literal/--regex/--dry-run flags present, default replacement [redacted]). check-secrets.mjs passes cleanly. However, `pm validate --check-history-drift` still reports 35 drifted items (13 hash + 34 chain mismatches) including pm-xk39 itself. The COMMAND is shipped; the legacy DRIFT cleanup is a separate operational task that does not block the command's acceptance criteria but needs a follow-up item to actually run history-redact / migration over the 35 streams."
  "2026-05-21T17:40:19.200Z",codex-gpt5,"Evidence 2026-05-21: privacy sub-agent found no raw credentials, but identified three legacy history entries with private operations topology details. Used pm history-redact, not direct JSONL edits, to redact pm-ny6y Caddy routing details, pm-r9ei telemetry topology/local evidence path details, and pm-vhdc remote health command details. Verification passed: pm history pm-ny6y --verify, pm history pm-r9ei --verify, pm history pm-vhdc --verify, and node scripts/check-secrets.mjs."
  "2026-05-22T20:29:16.384Z",claude-privacy-subagent,"Privacy/secret-leak sub-agent audit 2026-05-22 (claude-privacy-subagent). SCOPE: git-tracked files only (2087 total; 1675 under .agents/), incl 700+ history JSONL streams and all .toon items. RESULTS: (1) node scripts/check-secrets.mjs => exit 0, 'No credential-like secrets detected'. (2) gitignore confirmed: 'git ls-files scripts/prod' and 'git ls-files .env' both EMPTY (untracked). (3) IPv4 scan: ZERO real/private IPs in tracked files; only IPv4-shaped token across entire .agents tree is 127.0.0.1 (6x, localhost). Historical 16-file private-IP leak (pm-2326/pm-ny6y) confirmed already remediated to public domain names. (4) /home//Users absolute paths: ZERO in .agents; the only /home/ hits are test fixtures in tests/*.spec.ts asserting redaction logic (excluded by check-secrets excludeFiles ^tests/). (5) API tokens/keys: ZERO matches for AKIA/ghp_/gho_/sk-/sntrys_/sntryu_/glpat-/xox_/[pattern]/Bearer/npm_ anywhere in tracked files or .agents. (6) password/secret assignments: ZERO real hits. (7) Hostnames: pm-cli.unbrained.dev (13x, public telemetry API - intentional config, also in src/core/shared/constants.ts:201) and pm.unbrained.dev (5x, public Grafana hostname referenced in audit evidence) - both public DNS, NOT secrets, NO credentials attached. /tmp/pm-*-audit paths are ephemeral, non-sensitive. CANDIDATES & CLASSIFICATION: Total candidates examined ~6 unique. REAL_SECRET=0. FALSE_POSITIVE=all: [a] src/core/sentry/instrument.ts:129 Sentry DSN https://bf7...@o4510...ingest.de.sentry.io/4511... = client-side public ingest key (ships in npm package; grants event-send only, no data read); NOT in check-secrets ruleset (which only flags sntryu_/sntrys_ API tokens) = INTENTIONAL public config. [b] *.unbrained.dev hostnames = public infra DNS = intentional config. [c] [pattern] in tests/*.spec.ts = test fixtures. [d] 127.0.0.1 = localhost. REDACTIONS PERFORMED: NONE (no confirmed real secret in any tracked file). VERDICT: CLEAN. No files modified."
  "2026-05-23T08:27:46.890Z",codex-audit-2026-05-23,"Evidence: Used pm history-redact pm-rnpb to replace an absolute checkout path in the dogfood proposal with <repo>; command reported entries_changed=1, replacements=2, verify_ok=true. Rerunning node scripts/check-secrets.mjs and pm history pm-rnpb --verify."
  "2026-05-23T09:04:51.295Z",codex-observability-subagent-2026-05-23,"Privacy/history hygiene evidence 2026-05-23: tracked-file secret scan and changed history stream verification completed without source edits. Sanitized commands/results: node scripts/check-secrets.mjs => PASS, no credential-like secrets detected in tracked files. git diff --name-only -- .agents/pm/history => changed streams pm-rnpb, pm-swie, pm-xk39. pm history pm-rnpb --verify => ok=true entries=485 current_matches_latest=true. pm history pm-swie --verify => ok=true entries=8 current_matches_latest=true. pm history pm-xk39 --verify => ok=true entries=57 current_matches_latest=true. No new tracked secret found; no history-redact workflow needed in this pass."
  "2026-05-25T12:28:23.856Z",codex-reliability-history-agent,"Execution update 2026-05-25 for history integrity follow-through:\n\n- Moved item back to in_progress for active completion and claimed ownership under PM_AUTHOR codex-reliability-history-agent.\n- Added targeted lock-window conflict regression coverage across history mutation commands:\n  - tests/unit/history-activity-command.spec.ts: assert explicit conflict message + non-redaction when history changes before lock, and new branch coverage for item-changed-before-lock on history-redact.\n  - tests/unit/history-repair-command.spec.ts: assert explicit conflict message for item-changed-before-lock, preserve history stream snapshot, and new branch coverage for history-changed-before-lock.\n  - tests/unit/restore-command.spec.ts: assert explicit conflict message for history-changed-before-lock and new branch coverage for item-changed-before-lock while preserving pre-lock history stream.\n- Focused history integrity verification passed:\n  - node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/history-activity-command.spec.ts tests/unit/history-repair-command.spec.ts tests/unit/restore-command.spec.ts --reporter=dot (46 tests passed).\n- Manual temp-directory end-to-end flow passed in isolated PM_PATH/PM_GLOBAL_PATH sandbox:\n  - init -> create -> update -> append sensitive literal -> history-redact -> deliberate hash tamper -> history-repair -> restore(version 1) -> install npm:pm-changelog -> validate(history drift/resolution) -> health(brief).\n  - Result: history verify_ok=true after redaction/repair, drift counts zero, and all command exits successful.\n- Safety and observability checks passed on repository tracker after resetting temporary env overrides:\n  - node scripts/check-secrets.mjs\n  - pm health --check-only --brief --json\n  - pm validate --check-resolution --check-history-drift --json\n  - node scripts/release/sentry-telemetry-gate.mjs --json --telemetry-mode required --max-critical 10 --max-high 20 --max-telemetry-error-rate 10 --max-telemetry-missing-error-rows 0\n  - Gate result: sentry critical=0 high=4 (within threshold), telemetry finish_error_rate_pct=2.42, failures_without_error_code_rows=0."
